records.addlTxt:
Defendant Laniqua D Lyons in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 2 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.
Conditions:
*  AODA assessment/treatment;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety;
*  Complete a course in anger management;
*  Obtain/maintain full time employment/attend school;
*  Mental health evaluation/treatment;
*  Pay a fine of $100.00 including costs and surcharges to be paid by 01-06-2017 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Submit a DNA sample/pay the DNA surcharge.

Court denied defense request for expungement.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
